<item>
            <title>[JXPATH-162] Concurrency problem for JXPathContextFactory.factoryImplName static field</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JXPATH-162</link>
                <project id="12310480" key="JXPATH">Commons JXPath</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The static field &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;factoryImplName&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; is loaded lazily when the first call to JXPathContextFactory#getInstance() is made. This is a broken pattern when #getInstance() is called by multiple threads. My suggestion is to find the name in the static initializer:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;private static final String factoryImplName = findFactory(FACTORY_NAME_PROPERTY, DEFAULT_FACTORY_CLASS);&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
